# Hand-merged Jena subsystem lifecycle list.
#
# jena-core, jena-arq and jena-shacl each ship a META-INF/services/org.apache.jena.sys.JenaSubsystemLifecycle
# file at the SAME path. When the maven-bundle-plugin inlines the jars into this single OSGi
# bundle (Embed-Dependency inline=true), only one survives — so JenaSystem.init() would otherwise
# miss either jena-core init (no RDF model), RIOT/ARQ init (no Turtle parser / no SPARQL), or SHACL
# init (no shacl_validate). This project resource is processed first by bnd, so it wins the collision
# and lists the union from every jena jar. Keep in sync if the Jena version bumps (check each jena
# jar's copy of this file).
#
#   jena-core:  InitJenaCore
#   jena-arq:   InitRIOT, InitARQ, InitRDFS
#   jena-shacl: InitShacl
org.apache.jena.sys.InitJenaCore
org.apache.jena.riot.system.InitRIOT
org.apache.jena.sparql.system.InitARQ
org.apache.jena.rdfs.sys.InitRDFS
org.apache.jena.shacl.sys.InitShacl
